r\":\"#495057\",\"fontSize\":10},\"data\":[[[{\"xAxis\":\"2017-01-01\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"#2a6f9722\"},\"name\":\"Obama\"},{\"xAxis\":\"2017-01-20\"}],[{\"xAxis\":\"2017-01-20\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"#bc474922\"},\"name\":\"Trump I\"},{\"xAxis\":\"2021-01-20\"}],[{\"xAxis\":\"2021-01-20\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"#2a6f9722\"},\"name\":\"Biden\"},{\"xAxis\":\"2025-01-20\"}],[{\"xAxis\":\"2025-01-20\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"#bc474922\"},\"name\":\"Trump II*\"},{\"xAxis\":\"2026-04-01\"}]]]}}],\"tooltip\":{\"trigger\":\"axis\",\"valueFormatter\":\"function(v){ return typeof v==='number' ? v.toLocaleString() : v; }\"},\"dataZoom\":[{\"xAxisIndex\":0}],\"toolbox\":{\"feature\":{\"dataZoom\":[]}},\"title\":[{\"left\":\"center\",\"text\":\"Monthly US news volume about the presidency (Media Cloud)\",\"subtext\":\"Matching query: (\\\"white house\\\" OR president OR presidential); index grows over time\"}]},\"dispose\":true,\"theme2\":true,\"customTheme\":\"{\\n  \\\"color\\\": [\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#e07a5f\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#6a4c93\\\",\\\"#2f9e44\\\",\\\"#f2c14e\\\",\\\"#1d3557\\\",\\\"#6c757d\\\"],\\n  \\\"backgroundColor\\\": \\\"transparent\\\",\\n  \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"fontFamily\\\": \\\"system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif\\\" },\\n  \\\"title\\\": { \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"fontWeight\\\": \\\"600\\\" } },\\n  \\\"legend\\\": { \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#495057\\\" } },\\n  \\\"grid\\\": { \\\"containLabel\\\": true, \\\"left\\\": 48, \\\"right\\\": 24, \\\"top\\\": 56, \\\"bottom\\\": 40 },\\n  \\\"xAxis\\\": { \\\"axisLine\\\": { \\\"lineStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#adb5bd\\\" } } },\\n  \\\"yAxis\\\": { \\\"splitLine\\\": { \\\"lineStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#e9ecef\\\" } } }\\n}\",\"theme_name\":\"econ\"},\"evals\":[\"opts.tooltip.valueFormatter\"],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n## Per-admin media attention — avg stories / month (Media Cloud)\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"echarts4r html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-14deeba38857b2b087ff\" style=\"width:100%;height:500px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-14deeba38857b2b087ff\">{\"x\":{\"theme\":\"custom\",\"tl\":false,\"draw\":true,\"renderer\":\"canvas\",\"events\":[],\"buttons\":[],\"opts\":{\"yAxis\":[{\"show\":true,\"name\":\"Stories / month\"}],\"xAxis\":[{\"data\":[\"Bush (43)\",\"Obama\",\"Trump I\",\"Biden\",\"Trump II*\"],\"type\":\"category\",\"boundaryGap\":true}],\"legend\":{\"data\":[\"Avg stories / month\"]},\"series\":[{\"data\":[{\"value\":[\"Bush (43)\",\" 32046\"]},{\"value\":[\"Obama\",\"238439\"]},{\"value\":[\"Trump I\",\"840317\"]},{\"value\":[\"Biden\",\"614637\"]},{\"value\":[\"Trump II*\",\"655425\"]}],\"name\":\"Avg stories / month\",\"type\":\"bar\",\"yAxisIndex\":0,\"xAxisIndex\":0,\"coordinateSystem\":\"cartesian2d\",\"itemStyle\":{\"color\":\"function(p){ var c=[\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\"]; return c[p.dataIndex]; }\"}}],\"tooltip\":{\"trigger\":\"axis\",\"valueFormatter\":\"function(v){ return typeof v==='number' ? v.toLocaleString() : v; }\"},\"title\":[{\"left\":\"center\",\"text\":\"Average monthly Media Cloud story volume per administration\",\"subtext\":\"Raw Media Cloud counts — not corpus-normalized; later years have more indexed sources\"}]},\"dispose\":true,\"theme2\":true,\"customTheme\":\"{\\n  \\\"color\\\": [\\\"#2a6f97\\\",\\\"#e07a5f\\\",\\\"#bc4749\\\",\\\"#6a4c93\\\",\\\"#2f9e44\\\",\\\"#f2c14e\\\",\\\"#1d3557\\\",\\\"#6c757d\\\"],\\n  \\\"backgroundColor\\\": \\\"transparent\\\",\\n  \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"fontFamily\\\": \\\"system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif\\\" },\\n  \\\"title\\\": { \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"fontWeight\\\": \\\"600\\\" } },\\n  \\\"legend\\\": { \\\"textStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#495057\\\" } },\\n  \\\"grid\\\": { \\\"containLabel\\\": true, \\\"left\\\": 48, \\\"right\\\": 24, \\\"top\\\": 56, \\\"bottom\\\": 40 },\\n  \\\"xAxis\\\": { \\\"axisLine\\\": { \\\"lineStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#adb5bd\\\" } } },\\n  \\\"yAxis\\\": { \\\"splitLine\\\": { \\\"lineStyle\\\": { \\\"color\\\": \\\"#e9ecef\\\" } } }\\n}\",\"theme_name\":\"econ\"},\"evals\":[\"opts.series.0.itemStyle.color\",\"opts.tooltip.valueFormatter\"],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Caveats\n\n1. **Coverage starts 2017.** GDELT's GKG indexes articles globally, but for\n   this specific query the API returned daily tone data beginning in\n   January 2017. Pre-2017 admins show NA.\n\n2. **Tone is lexicon-based.** GDELT counts positive and negative valence\n   words in each article. It does not understand *who the article is about*\n   or *what the author's intent is*. A headline like \"Biden condemns Putin\"\n   registers as negative because of \"condemns,\" even though Biden is the\n   subject speaking against a negative event.\n\n3. **US-English-only slice.** The query filters to `sourcelang:eng\n   sourcecountry:US`. International and non-English coverage is excluded —\n   which matters because global news framing often differs from US framing.\n\n4. **Query is a keyword proxy.** `\"white house\" OR president OR\n   presidential` catches most US executive-branch coverage but is not an\n   exact match for \"articles about the sitting president.\"\n\n5. **Volume varies by era.** Later years have denser news indexing, so the\n   stability of averages is not uniform. The `tone_months` column in the\n   table shows effective sample size per admin.\n\n## Attribution & license\n\n### GDELT — tone\n\nTone data sourced from the **GDELT Project** (*Global Database of Events,\nLanguage, and Tone*). The GDELT project is a collaboration of Google\nJigsaw with founders Kalev Leetaru and Philip Schrodt. Data made available\nunder **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial (CC-BY-NC)**. See\n<https://www.gdeltproject.org/>.\n\n### Media Cloud — volume\n\nStory volume data sourced from **Media Cloud**, an open-source media\nresearch platform operated by a consortium including the MIT Center for\nCivic Media and the Berkman Klein Center for Internet & Society. Counts\nretrieved from the Media Cloud Search API (total-count endpoint). Media\nCloud data is made available for academic research under their terms of\nservice: <https://mediacloud.org/>.\n\n### Non-commercial use\n\nThis site's use of all media-analytics data (GDELT, Media Cloud) is\nnon-commercial: the site carries no ads, sells no products, and is\npublished for public educational research.\n\n## Where to go next\n\n- **[Economic Sentiment →](economic.qmd)** — UMCSENT consumer-mood timeline.\n- **[Political Approval →](approval.qmd)** — Gallup per-admin averages.\n- **[Methodology →](about.qmd)** — full caveats across all three sections.\n",
